                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13959466" author="kzhang" created="Fri, 4 Apr 2014 00:15:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;JettyUtils.startJettyServer() used to bind to all interfaces, however, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1060&quot; title=&quot;JettyUtil is not using host information to start server&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-1060&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-1060&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; change that to only bind to a specific interface (preferably a non-loopback address).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you want to revert to previous behavior, here&apos;s the patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/318&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/318&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13963468" author="pwendell" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2014 21:31:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay we fixed this for 1.0. The decision was just to revert to the old behavior of binding to all interfaces. Note that this means SPARK_LOCAL_IP is not relevant for the UI.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
